Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane is condemning the killing of four people, including three pensioners this week. Courtesy #DStv403 PORT ELIZABETH - Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane is condemning the killing of four people, including three pensioners this week. Three elderly women and a man were stabbed to death in Lady Frere. WATCH:  No arrests yet as police investigate Shallcross murders Mabuyane is urging men to stop the war against women, and focus on the fight against COVID-19. He says he's hoping all culprits will be behind bars.